Dialogue 1: Renting a Room（租房场景）「住宿/设施/家具/交通/费用类词汇全覆盖」
Male (Agent): Good morning, City Accommodation Agency. How can I assist you today?
Female (Tenant): Good morning. I’m a university student majoring in anthropology, and I need to find accommodation near the campus. Do you have any apartment or flat available in the residential suburb or central town?
Male: Sure. We have two great options: a shared flat in the outskirts (10 mins by bus to campus) and a single bedroom in a high-rise building on Main Street (5 mins walk to the railway station). What’s your priority for the surroundings?
Female: The single bedroom please—I need a quiet space for study, so no disturbance is a must. What’s the rent per month, and does it include utility bills like electricity and water?
Male: It’s 450 pounds per month, all utilities included, plus free internet access. The flat has a private bathroom with a shower and water heater, a shared kitchen with a fridge, microwave oven and washing machine, and basic furniture: a desk, chair, bed (double size) and a wardrobe with drawers.
Female: Perfect. Is there a parking spot for a bicycle? I ride a cycle to campus every day. Also, what’s the deposit requirement?
Male: Yes, there’s a garage for bicycles and small vehicles—free of charge. The deposit is 300 pounds, fully refundable if there’s no damage to the facility or furniture when you move out. You can move in next Monday if you confirm today.
Female: Great. Do I need to sign a contract? And who’s responsible for repair if the equipment breaks?
Male: Yes, a 12-month contract—we’ll also give you a welcome package with the community code and rules. We cover repair for normal wear; man-made damage is your cost. Can I get your surname and phone number for reservation?
Female: My surname is Green, and my number is 07896543210. One last thing: is the building soundproof? I hate noise.
Male: Totally—all rooms are soundproof, and the neighbouring residents are all students, so it’s very quiet. I’ll meet you at the building entrance at 2 PM tomorrow for a viewing if you’d like.
Female: That’s perfect. See you tomorrow!
Male: See you then, Ms. Green.
Dialogue 2: Enrolling in a University Course（课程报名场景）「学科/学习/证书/费用/人员类词汇全覆盖」
Male (Clerk): Good afternoon, University Admission Office. Can I help you with enrolment or registration for a course?
Female (Student): Good afternoon. I want to enrol in an undergraduate major in linguistics, and I need to check the curriculum for the first semester. What subjects are included, and is there an orientation for new students?
Male: Sure. The first semester has core subjects: physical physics, applied science, geography, history and language studies. We have a 2-day orientation next week, and you’ll get a textbook list and library card on the first day. Are you a freshman or a transfer student?
Female: A freshman—I’m an overseas applicant from China. What’s the tuition fee for the full-time course, and are there any scholarship or grant options for international students?
Male: The annual tuition is 12,000 pounds, and we offer scholarships for high-score applicants (up to 5,000 pounds). You can also apply for a financial loan from the bank on campus. The fee is payable in two parts: half in September, half in January.
Female: Great. What about the study requirements? How many lectures, tutorials and seminars are there per week, and is there a minimum attendance rate?
Male: 15 sessions per week: 8 lectures, 4 tutorials and 3 seminars. The minimum attendance is 80%—if you miss too many, you’ll have to resit the assessment. Each term has a final exam, and your mark is a mix of exam score and assignment performance.
Female: Understood. What assignments do I need to complete? I’ve heard there’s a research project and a presentation for each subject.
Male: Exactly—one research paper (with abstract and bibliography) and one oral presentation per subject, with a strict deadline for each. Our professors and tutors will give feedback to help you with revision. You’ll also have access to the laboratory for experiments in biology and chemistry.
Female: Perfect. What facilities are available for students? I need a laptop for study—is there a computer lab on campus?
Male: Yes—we have 5 computer labs with free laser printing, a library with all kinds of publications (journals, newspapers, encyclopedias) and a lecture theatre with a whiteboard and overhead projector. We also have a noticeboard in the reception for all important information.
Female: I’d like to register today. What documents do I need to provide?
Male: Your application form, degree certificate (high school), photo ID and a signature form. I’ll process your registration now, and you’ll get your student ID card in 3 working days.
Female: Here are all the documents. Thank you so much!
Male: You’re welcome. Welcome to our university, Ms. Green!
Dialogue 3: Using the University Library（图书馆场景）「图书馆专属/出版物/学生种类词汇全覆盖」
Male (Librarian): Good morning, University Central Library. Can I assist you with borrowing books, catalog searching or getting a library card?
Female (Student): Good morning. I’m a new sophomore majoring in literature, and I need to borrow some reference books for my research assignment on history. First, how do I use the library catalog to find books, and what’s the due date for borrowing?
Male: First, scan your library card at the delivery desk to access the internet system—the catalog is sorted by classification and category. You can borrow up to 10 books at a time, with a due date of 4 weeks. If you need more time, you can apply for renewal online (max 2 times).
Female: What if I return a book overdue? Do I have to pay a fine?
Male: Yes—the fine is 0.5 pounds per day per book, and if a book is out on loan to another student, you can put a reserve on it, and we’ll send you a pink slip when it’s available. We also offer interlibrary service if we don’t have the book you need.
Female: Understood. I need some periodicals and journals on sociology—where are they located? Also, are the open shelves or close shelves for reference books only?
Male: Periodicals and journals are on the 3rd floor, stack area C. Close shelves are for closed reserve books (reference only, no borrowing), and open shelves are for all borrowable books—you can take them directly and check out at the delivery desk.
Male: Also, we have a card index for old publications, and a copy machine on the 2nd floor (5 pence per page). Do you need a handout with the library facility map?
Female: Yes, please. One more question: can I book a study room for a group discussion? My classmates and I need to prepare a presentation next week.
Male: Sure—there are 10 group study rooms on the 4th floor, you can book them online for 2 hours per session. The rooms have a microphone and video equipment for presentation practice.
Female: Perfect. I also need to print my bibliography—where is the laser printing room?
Male: On the 1st floor, next to the reception. You can use your student ID card to pay for printing. If you have any other questions, the librarians at the information desk are always here to help.
Female: Thank you so much for your guidance!
Male: You’re welcome. Enjoy using the library!
Dialogue 4: Medical Consultation（医疗咨询场景）「症状/疾病/药品/医生/医疗词汇全覆盖」
Male (Receptionist): Good morning, City Clinic. How can I help you—are you here for a pre-booking or a walk-in appointment with a physician?
Female (Patient): Good morning. I have a sore throat, fever (38℃) and a cough for 3 days, and I also feel dizzy and drowsy—I need a doctor as soon as possible. Do you have any appointments available today?
Male: I’m sorry to hear that. Dr. Smith, our senior physician, has a slot at 2 PM today—would that be convenient? He’s an expert in treating the flu and respiratory infections.
Female: That’s perfect. Do I need to bring any documents, and what’s the consultation fee?
Male: Just your ID card—if you have medical records from a previous clinic, bring those too. The fee is 40 pounds, and we accept cash, credit card or bank transfer. We also have a chemist's on-site for any medicine the doctor prescribes.
Female: Great. I’ll arrive 15 minutes early. One quick question: what if the doctor prescribes antibiotics or injections? Are they available on-site?
Male: Yes—our clinic has all basic medicines: capsules, pills, aspirin, vitamins, ointments, syrups and tablets, and we can do injections and X-rays on-site too. The doctor will also take your temperature and check your blood pressure during the consultation.
Female: Thank you. I also have a stiff neck from sleeping wrong—can the doctor check that too?
Male: Absolutely—Dr. Smith can also give you a prescription for a painkiller cream for your neck, and some advice on relaxation to ease the pain.
Female: Perfect. See you at 2 PM!
Male: See you then, Ms. Green. We hope you feel better soon!
