Male: Max 15 tourists per group—small groups for a better experience, and it’s very safe (we provide a helmet for the hike and a safety brief at the start). We also have a tour planner to share the itinerary with you in advance.
Female: Perfect. What do I need to bring? And is there a dress code for the church visit?
Male: Comfortable walking shoes, a jacket (coastal weather is windy), a camera and your passport (for ID). The church has a casual dress code—no fancy wear, just cover your shoulders and knees. We’ll also give you a brochure with the location map and postcode of all spots.
Male: We also have optional activities: skiing (if you want to go to the nearby mountain) and a visit to the zoo with local wildlife—each is an extra 20 pounds.
Female: I’ll skip the optional activities, just the main tour. Can I book for one person, and what’s the deposit requirement?
Male: Yes—deposit is 50 pounds, the rest is payable on the first day of the tour. Can I get your name, phone number and email for confirmation?
Female: Lucy Green, 07896543210, lucy.green@gmail.com.
Male: I’ve sent the confirmation email with the tour details and meeting point (London train station entrance at 8 AM on Saturday). See you then!
Female: Thank you so much!
Male: You’re welcome—have a great tour!
